name: Gasthof Hotel Zur Post
description: Bavarian cuisine and beers at a country pub/eatery with rooms, plus a relaxed bistro and a beer garde.

name: Bräustüberls Schloss Seefeld
description: Nice old style and large restaurant within the Seefeld Castle. They serve good Bavarian food and drinks. Their dessers are really good too.

name: Döneria Feinkost
description: This is the place to go if you want to have a Donner Kebap. It is fast, attendants are nice and smile often, and the food is delicious.

name: Brauhaus Herrsching
description: Beer garden and Bavarian restaurant. With a large menu and lot of beer to offer. We like to dress up like in the middle ages.

name: Colosseum
description: Italian Restaurant, with nearly the best Tiramisu, all sort of Pizzas and Pasta. We can bring the food to you too.

name: Steg 32
description: Restaurand and Lounge. Elegant lakeside space with a terrace prepaing local and internation dishes, plus wine and cocktails.

name: Seaside Sushi & Sake
description: Sushi, maki and sashimi plates, plus soups, tempura and gyoza dumplings, at a simple venue.

name: Pier 48
description: Bright, contemporary venue with a wooden patio, offering Mediterranean and international fare. Dine-in, Curbside pickup. No delivery.

name: Nefis Döner Bistro
description: Small restaurant and takeaway service dedicated to the cult of Döner. Lots of ingredients available. Cheap. Nice. Jammy.

name: La Dolce Vita
description: Pizza, pasta and Italian seafood in an eatery with a waterfront terrace and views of a lake jetty.

name: Restaurant Seespitz
description: Pasta, grill dishes and beer in an elegant, contemporary restaurant with a lakefront terrace.

name: Indische Ganpati Herrsching
description: Indian restaurant, with original Indian specialties, being as hot as in India.

name: Volcano Grill
description: Grill terrace restaurant, hidden in a place no one would expect to find a restaurant, I can't even imagine that was a restaurant... I wonder how they make a living...

name: Matos Fischladen
description: Takeaway fish snacks and sandwiches. Fresh fish from who knows where... but it seems tasty... Isn't it pork looking like fish?

name: Andechser Hof
description: Seriously? They serve food to all schools in the neighbourhood, no wonder why every other child wants to go back home for lunch.

name: IPHO Vietnamese Cuisine
description: Well care, modern looking Vietnamese restaurant, with a large variety of dishes.

name: See Heimat
description: Tiny restaurant with a large terrace, serving a very limited menu of Bavarian food and beer. It's close to the lake. And they smile more than in the average German restaurants.

name: Fischsemmel König
description: Yet another takeaway post, offering fish sandwiches. They are jammy.

name: De Victorie
description: Very modern restaurant, with seafood and classic Belgian food. Nice surroundings, great for a walk after lunch.

name: Tuincafé 'In den Hof'
description: More a bar than a restaurant, but they serve food too. Honestly, with all the good restaurants in the neighbourhood, I wonder why Google list this one almost at the top. I was here long ago.

name: Naroj
description: Google says this is a restaurant. But look at the photos... Not sure what it looks like.

name: De frietverslinder BV
description: Fried food, all sorts, I passed by the front of this place for years and never thought it was a restaurant. But the photos show food. So it has to be.

name: Barba
description: I had lunch and dinner here a lot, it's in Leuven. It's expensive. But they cook really good. I don't know what else to say. I just discovered that most of the restaurants listed in Google don't have a description. Unbelievable.

name: EED
description: Small cozy restaurant, serving Belgian specialties, and making the stay a pleasure. If it's really the one I think it is.

name: Lust Bold Bistro
description: Another nice looking restaurant in the area of Leuven, serving international dishes and Belgian specialties. In Summer we like to do grill.
